    "description": {
      "value": "<p>To use this technique, your katana must be sheathed in a solid sheath (such as wood or metal). You make an attack against the target, as though performing Kenjutsu: Iaido. Regardless of the result, you make a second attack with the sword's sheath at a -4 penalty, which is treated as a katana of one (metal) or two (wooden) sizes smaller than the katana it is paired with.<br><br>Unlike Iaido, this technique cannot be used as part of a charge. When this technique has been performed, your katana will be unsheathed, and you will hold the sheath in your off-hand.</p>\n\n\n\n",
